Press any key to begin.

You will use the "e" and "i" computer keys to categorize items into groups as fast as you can. These are the four groups and the items that belong to each:

Good:
Enjoy, Smiling, Glorious, Beautiful, Fantastic, Friend, Cheer, Joyous

Bad:
Awful, Bothersome, Pain, Nasty, Hurtful, Rotten, Evil, Annoy

African Americans:


European Americans:


There are seven parts. The instructions change for each part. Pay attention!

Press any key to continue.

Press e for:
European Americans

Press i for:
African Americans

Put a left finger on the e key for items that belong to the European Americans People category. Put a right finger on the i key for items that belong to the African Americans People category. Items will appear one at a time.

If you make a mistake, a red X will appear. Press the keys listed below to continue. Go as fast as you can while being accurate.

Press the any key when you are ready to start.
